<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="651" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363 Barco/156½: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Piles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-28T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 28,
                                        1928—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>46. On account of Folsom’s telegram to his company latter prefers not to
                            instruct him to make written statement. Accordingly take no further
                            action on instructions contained in Department’s 45, August 25,
                            noon.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>